<h1>Main tournament</h1>

<p>The tournament is open to anyone who wants to compete with the best pinball players in the world. We have a maximum number of participants set to 175 (see <a href="?page=registration">Registration</a>). All players are first playing a qualification round, to get a place in the playoffs on Sunday. The playoffs boil down to a final round deciding who is to become <span style='font-weight: bold;'>the European Champion 2007</span>. Please note, women and men compete on the same conditions and therefore we do not separate them into different classes. However, to encourage more women to play we give the best woman a price.<br/><br/>

<i>Changes 2007-06-10: Added more information on how the qualification and playoffs are to be carried out. Changes are marked in <span class="changes">red</span>. Note that the final and possibly the semifinals will be videotaped and live feeded to a big screen. The recording might also be included in a british documentary.</i></p><br/><br/>



<h2>The Qualifying</h2>

<p>Each player gets to play 5 random machines from the qualifying bank, two credits on each machine. The best result on each machine is then measured against the other players that played the same machine and qualifying points are awarded based on how well you rank compared to the others. Your total amount of qualifying points on the five machines you play gives you your total qualifying score. This score is ranked in comparison to all the other players' total qualifying score. The players having the 48 highest total qualifying scores make it to the playoffs.<br/><br/>

