<h3>Qualification round</h3>

<p><span class="changes">
  1) Two players typically qualify at the same machine at the same time, i.e. they play two 2-player games. The order of play is: For the first try the lowest player-number starts and for the second try the order is reversed.<br/>
  2) If you can motivate (to an official) why a specific machine is inappropriate for two-player games, you can be allowed to play one player at a time, i.e. one-player games.<br/>
  3) No practicing on the machines is allowed.<br/>
  4) The scorekeepers start games and write down the scores. The players do not!<br/>
  5) The 48 best players advance to the playoffs. In case of a draw, the players are ranked according to the best individual position on any of their qualifying machines. If there is still a tie and the tie is regarding 48th or 24th place they play a deciding game on a random machine. Start order is decided by a coin flip. In all other undecided draws the qualification rank is decided by coin flip.<br/>
  6) Be there well ahead of the start of your qualification round.
</span></p><br/><br/>



<h2>The Playoffs</h2>

<h3>Playoffs</h3>
<p><span class="changes">
  1) A practice round of one minute per player is offered before each game is played.<br/>
  2) Choice of starting order (or position in the final) begins at the player with the highest qualifying rank.<br/>
  3) Make sure you are in the playoffs area well in time for your matches.<br/>
  4) At the first round of the playoffs, where Q25 to Q48 play, there will be a "call out". If any player is missing, the highest ranked non-qualified player takes Q48.
</ol></span></p>


